    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
        <title>CYLINDER HEAD REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean valve faces and seats with a suitable cleaning solvent to remove all dirt or foreign
                material. Blow dry all new and used components using filtered compressed air.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thoroughly clean all valve guides, prior to valve installation, as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coat a brush (
                    <emph type="bold">OEM6343</emph>) with soap and water as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050452">4.52</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Brush must have a slightly larger diameter than the I.D. of the valve guide.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert brush into valve guide bore and clean with a turning motion to insure removal of
                    any deposits.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Dry with filtered compressed air.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>PERFORM VALVE GUIDE BORE CLEANING ON:</para>
                        <seqlist style="arabic">
                            <item>
                                <para>NEW SERVICE VALVE GUIDES.</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>VALVE GUIDES INSTALLED IN NEW</para>
                                <para>SERVICE CYLINDER HEADS (LESS VALVE).</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>VALVE GUIDES PRESENTLY INSTALLED</para>
                                <para>IN CYLINDER HEAD, WHICH MEET BORE</para>
                                <para>SPECIFICATIONS.</para>
                            </item>
                        </seqlist>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the valve stems with clean engine oil and insert the valves into the valve
                guides.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the I.D. of the new valve stem seal assemblies with clean engine oil and install
                them over the valve and valve guide as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050453">4.53</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
                <emph type="bold"></emph>Be sure the seal assemblies are seated down against the cylinder head spring
                pockets.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050452" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1706" filename="../figeg1/eg1706.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.52.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Brush</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Valve Guide</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050453" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2330" filename="../figeg2/eg2330.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.53.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Valve Guide</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Valve Stem Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Stem Seal</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the valve spring over the stem seal assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be sure to install proper valve spring at proper valve location. Failure to properly locate
                        the springs could cause engine damage.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rotator assembly over the valve spring. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050454">4.54</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Snap new rotator seals into bottom side (rotator cone) of valve rotators before installing
                        rotator assembly on engine.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress the valve spring and install the spring locks (keepers) as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050455">4.55</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050454" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1691" filename="../figeg1/eg1691.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.54.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Valve Spring</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Valve Rotator</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050455" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2312" filename="../figeg2/eg2312.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.55.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Spring Compressor</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Spring Lock (keepers)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
